Renocolonic fistula complicating vesicorenal reflux and xanthogranulomatous pyelonephritis in a 20-month-old child. A case of vesico-renal reflux with xanthogranulomatous pyelonephritis complicated with a renocolic fistula in a 20 months old child is reported. Imaging in this case was crucial for the diagnosis and the work up it included ASP, renal ultrasound, UIV retrograde cystography and CT. The treatment consisted in a right ureteronephrectomy after fistula's section.